Description . Male ( Holotype ). Carapace and legs yellowish. Chelicerae orange. Labium and endites orange at tips and yellow at bases. Sternum yellow. Palps and legs grayish with sparse black stripes. Abdomen dorsally grayishwith 6–7 black chevrons, ventrally white (
Fig. 14 A
). Total length 2.1 . Carapace length 1.1 , width 0.75 . PME separated by their diameter. Palp measurements: femur 0.7 long, patella 0.25 long, tibia 0.35 long, 0.2 wide.

Leg measurements: I femur 1.4 / patella 0.5 / tibia 1.8 / metatarsus 1.4 / tarsus 0.8 / total 5.4 ; II 1.1 / 0.4 / 1.2 / 0.9 / 0.6 / 4.2 ; III 0.8 / 0.4 / 0.7 / 0.7 / 0.5 / 3.1 ; IV 1.1 / 0.4 / 1.1 / 1.1 / 0.6 / 4.3 . Palp: tibiae longer than cymbium, with two spines (
Fig. 16 B‒G
). Abdomen 1.2 long.
